Example model

formula <- migration ~ 
                        edges + 
                        sender("Population") + 
                        receiver("Population") +
                        sender("Population_Density") +
                        receiver("Population_Density") +
                        sender("GDP") +
                        receiver("GDP") +
                        sender("Crime_Index") +
                        receiver("Crime_Index") +
                        nodematch("Language") +
                        netcov(borders) +
                        in2stars(alpha = 0.8) +
                        out2stars(alpha = 0.8) +
                        mutual(alpha = 0.8)


model <- GERGM::gergm(formula,
                      covariate_data = covariates,
                      number_of_networks_to_simulate = 40000,
                      thin = 1/100,
                      proposal_variance = 0.05,
                      MCMC_burnin = 10000,
                      seed = 456,
                      convergence_tolerance = 0.5,
                      maximum_number_of_theta_updates = 10,
                      maximum_number_of_lambda_updates = 10)
